cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about improving the robustness of neural dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for improving the accuracy of the models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of negative sampling and the mention of neural networks also suggest that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses a new dataset and the evaluation of models, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
